[[!ftemplate id=tool]]

AbiWord is a word processor. It is written using Gtk+3 and provides an
embeddable widget called [[AbiWidget|http://www.abisource.com/wiki/AbiWidget]]
that can be loaded into other Gtk+3 applications.

It can be extended with plugins that can extend functionality. These can
be used to add more import/export file formats.

## Description

- [[Screenshots of the GUI|http://abisource.com/help/en-US/tutorial/window.html]]
- Spell-checking can use [[aspell|http://aspell.net/]], [[ispell|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ispell]], or [[enchant|http://www.abisource.com/projects/enchant/]]
- [[Menus|http://abisource.com/help/en-US/interface/index.html]] are described in the manual
- Bidirectional text support
- AbiSource also hosts [[several related projects|http://abisource.com/projects/]].
  - In particular, the [[Link Grammar|http://abisource.com/projects/link-grammar/]] natural langage parser.
  - An unmaintained library for pen input: [[libstylus|http://abisource.com/projects/libstylus/]]
- Collaborative editing: [[AbiCollab|http://www.abisource.com/wiki/AbiCollab]]

